in our organization.

495
00:23:09.764 --> 00:23:11.265
This is our nephew...

496
00:23:11.766 --> 00:23:12.767
<i>Breeze.</i>

497
00:23:13.810 --> 00:23:17.772
[chuckles] So. you. uh.
you ever consider that. uh.

498
00:23:17.939 --> 00:23:19.607
Hurricane or Tornado

499
00:23:19.774 --> 00:23:21.984
or maybe even Typhoon

500
00:23:22.151 --> 00:23:24.320
might have sounded
a little stronger?

501
00:23:25.988 --> 00:23:28.533
I ain't all stormy like that.
though. boss.

502
00:23:29.242 --> 00:23:31.869
I float in. float out.

503
00:23:32.787 --> 00:23:34.705
<i>coolin' shit along the way.</i>

504
00:23:35.832 --> 00:23:37.083
Breeze.

505
00:23:38.126 --> 00:23:42.964
And I believe you're familiar
with our resident boy wonder.

506
00:23:43.089 --> 00:23:44.340
<i>Kanan Stark.</i>

507
00:23:45.091 --> 00:23:46.134
Him I know.

508
00:23:46.300 --> 00:23:47.760
[tense music playing]

509
00:23:47.885 --> 00:23:49.345
[Snaps] <i>Mm-hmm.</i>

510
00:23:49.512 --> 00:23:55.351
He's a recent. but exciting.
addition to the team.

511
00:23:55.476 --> 00:23:57.311
[Stefano] <i>It's my understanding
that. uh.</i>

512
00:23:57.478 --> 00:24:01.065
you plan on having Unique
join this fuckin' party here.

513
00:24:02.525 --> 00:24:06.863
I'm assuming you know
that he was allied

514
00:24:06.988 --> 00:24:10.116
with the now late
cocksucker Phil Russo.

515
00:24:10.241 --> 00:24:12.702
[Pop] <i>Yeah. but Unique's
still got people out here.</i>

516
00:24:12.869 --> 00:24:15.204
It's not that easy
to just move past him.

517
00:24:15.371 --> 00:24:16.664
I disagree.

518
00:24:16.831 --> 00:24:19.667
[dramatic musical sting]

519
00:24:20.251 --> 00:24:21.544
<i>♪ Yo. check it ♪</i>

520
00:24:21.711 --> 00:24:22.879
["Ain't No Love" playing]

521
00:24:23.045 --> 00:24:24.714
You work as a call girl too. right?

522
00:24:25.506 --> 00:24:28.009
[Jennifer] I'm sorry.
I got confused.

523
00:24:28.885 --> 00:24:30.165
I thought you were someone else.

524
00:24:30.219 --> 00:24:32.263
I don't know
what you talkin' 'bout.

525
00:24:33.723 --> 00:24:35.016
I'm paying you for your time.

526
00:24:35.183 --> 00:24:36.934
<i>♪ Trust no one Not even a few ♪</i>

527
00:24:37.101 --> 00:24:38.912
<i>♪ Got some things on my chest
Gotta kick my truth... ♪</i>

528
00:24:38.936 --> 00:24:41.397
I just wanna know if you ever
tricked in Manhattan.

529
00:24:41.564 --> 00:24:43.357
And if you did.
who was runnin' that work.

530
00:24:43.524 --> 00:24:45.234
I only escort
in the outer boroughs.

531
00:24:45.943 --> 00:24:47.423
It's mostly high-end work
in Manhattan

532
00:24:47.570 --> 00:24:49.405
and you need
a four-year degree for that.

533
00:24:49.572 --> 00:24:50.740
And who pimpin' in the city?

534
00:24:50.907 --> 00:24:52.700
Flossie Siegel's
got all the best girls.

535
00:24:52.867 --> 00:24:54.118
Know how I can get to her?

536
00:24:54.285 --> 00:24:56.412
[Jennifer] <i>Nah.
But I'd be careful.</i>

537
00:24:56.954 --> 00:24:58.331
Flossie can be real scary.

538
00:24:58.998 --> 00:25:02.043
<i>♪ We go back and forth ♪</i>

539
00:25:02.210 --> 00:25:04.295
<i>♪ Back and forth ♪</i>

540
00:25:05.129 --> 00:25:06.631
I can be real scary too.

541
00:25:06.797 --> 00:25:09.342
♪♪

542
00:25:09.508 --> 00:25:10.968
[song fades]

543
00:25:11.135 --> 00:25:12.553
[machine whirring]

544
00:25:12.720 --> 00:25:15.223
["Get Money" playing]

545
00:25:15.389 --> 00:25:17.683
How the fuck you gon' have
that meeting without me?

546
00:25:18.267 --> 00:25:19.894
<i>You sayin' we 'bout
to be partners</i>

547
00:25:20.061 --> 00:25:22.289
but you havin' parlays about
this business behind my back?

548
00:25:22.313 --> 00:25:24.106
You didn't miss nothin'. 'Nique.

549
00:25:24.273 --> 00:25:25.566
Just that Italian telling us

550
00:25:25.733 --> 00:25:27.336
he don't wanna get close
to the work no more

551
00:25:27.360 --> 00:25:28.903
but he still want his piece.

552
00:25:29.070 --> 00:25:30.821
Lil' Linguini said that?

553
00:25:32.198 --> 00:25:33.950
The fish guy. Stefano?

554
00:25:34.075 --> 00:25:35.117
Yeah. Him.

555
00:25:35.243 --> 00:25:37.370
Motherfucker got no love for me.

556
00:25:37.495 --> 00:25:38.871
Shit. I was working
with the nigga

557
00:25:39.038 --> 00:25:40.248
who poked a knife into him.

558
00:25:40.414 --> 00:25:42.291
Stefano not thinkin'
'bout you. man.

559
00:25:42.458 --> 00:25:43.626
He just want his money.

560
00:25:43.793 --> 00:25:44.793
[loud slam]

561
00:25:45.336 --> 00:25:47.713
I know y'all tryin'
to cut me out this deal.

562
00:25:48.047 --> 00:25:49.131
Straight up. nigga.

563
00:25:49.757 --> 00:25:51.467
you ain't foolin' nobody
wit' your garbage

564
00:25:51.634 --> 00:25:53.928
<i>about your options
and opportunities.</i>

565
00:25:54.637 --> 00:25:56.555
You ain't got nothin'
but what we offerin'.

566
00:25:57.098 --> 00:26:00.601
All this flexin' and beefin'
is straight vapor. nigga.

567
00:26:00.768 --> 00:26:02.144
[tense music playing]

568
00:26:02.311 --> 00:26:04.730
Maybe you got some
stray soldiers here and there

569
00:26:05.231 --> 00:26:06.983
but they ain't got nothin'
to fight for.

570
00:26:07.984 --> 00:26:09.318
They fight for me.

571
00:26:10.486 --> 00:26:12.405
They fight
for whoever feedin' 'em.

572
00:26:13.281 --> 00:26:15.324
And you ain't that nigga
no more.

573
00:26:23.416 --> 00:26:24.709
None of that matter anyway

574
00:26:24.875 --> 00:26:26.711
'cause you ain't gettin' cut
outta any deal.

575
00:26:28.504 --> 00:26:31.132
You in this. We partners.

576
00:26:31.716 --> 00:26:33.134
Believe that. 'Nique.

577
00:26:34.593 --> 00:26:36.512
♪♪

578
00:26:36.637 --> 00:26:38.014
I got you.

579
00:26:38.556 --> 00:26:39.724
<i>Yeah.</i>

580
00:26:42.351 --> 00:26:44.312
[music fades]

581
00:26:47.023 --> 00:26:50.526
I made a lot of money
with Joaquin over the years.

582
00:26:51.736 --> 00:26:55.614
Which is why I agreed
to meet with you.

583
00:26:56.782 --> 00:26:57.950
But...

584
00:26:58.993 --> 00:27:00.578
I gotta tell you...

585
00:27:01.871 --> 00:27:04.040
our friend Stefano.

586
00:27:04.832 --> 00:27:07.001
he doesn't speak fondly of you.

587
00:27:07.168 --> 00:27:09.128
I could say the same thing
about him.

588
00:27:09.295 --> 00:27:10.295
but I won't.

589
00:27:10.963 --> 00:27:12.274
When you talkin' about
other people

590
00:27:12.298 --> 00:27:13.442
it's 'cause you ain't got
nothin' good

591
00:27:13.466 --> 00:27:14.550
to say about yourself.

592
00:27:16.969 --> 00:27:19.555
So you wanna be in business
in Manhattan?

593
00:27:19.722 --> 00:27:21.265
[Raq] <i>There's an opportunity
here.</i>

594
00:27:22.308 --> 00:27:23.392
For both of us.

595
00:27:23.559 --> 00:27:24.560
[Pino] <i>But. um...</i>

596
00:27:25.144 --> 00:27:27.271
why would I go around
Stefano's back?

597
00:27:27.438 --> 00:27:29.190
Because we're not
goin' around his back.

598
00:27:30.149 --> 00:27:32.068
We doin' it right in front
of his fuckin' face.

599
00:27:32.651 --> 00:27:35.488
Which. knowing you people.
is just how you like to do it.

600
00:27:35.613 --> 00:27:39.033
[tense music playing]

601
00:27:39.200 --> 00:27:41.035
You know us too well.

602
00:27:43.204 --> 00:27:45.164
[music fades]

603
00:27:45.331 --> 00:27:47.208
You movin' in?

604
00:27:48.125 --> 00:27:49.668
[sighs] Oh. shit.

605
00:27:50.795 --> 00:27:51.879
Damn.

606
00:27:52.463 --> 00:27:53.714
You scared me. Shirley.

607
00:27:54.340 --> 00:27:56.050
Saw that van parked out front

608
00:27:56.217 --> 00:27:58.636
with some guy standing guard.

609
00:27:59.261 --> 00:28:00.513
I wondered what was going on.

610
00:28:00.679 --> 00:28:02.599
I thought maybe the bank
was finally taking over.

611
00:28:02.723 --> 00:28:03.891
[laughs]

612
00:28:04.058 --> 00:28:05.393
Nah. Um...

613
00:28:05.559 --> 00:28:07.812
just need to keep some shit
here for a minute.

614
00:28:08.771 --> 00:28:10.106
What's in the boxes?

615
00:28:10.272 --> 00:28:12.066
[dramatic music playing]

616
00:28:12.233 --> 00:28:15.361
Nothin'. You know. um.
just some bullshit.

617
00:28:16.404 --> 00:28:18.531
Bullshit? Yeah.

618
00:28:19.073 --> 00:28:20.616
That sounds about right.

619
00:28:25.371 --> 00:28:27.957
-[traffic buzzing]
-[music fades]

620
00:28:28.124 --> 00:28:30.042
Manhattan ain't Queens

621
00:28:30.209 --> 00:28:31.877
and Queens ain't Manhattan.

622
00:28:32.044 --> 00:28:35.131
But what works there
doesn't work here. vice versa.

623
00:28:35.256 --> 00:28:36.507
<i>By and large.</i>

624
00:28:37.174 --> 00:28:40.803
we got a far more sophisticated
clientele here.

625
00:28:41.345 --> 00:28:42.665
So the Tiparillos
you been selling

626
00:28:42.721 --> 00:28:44.348
on the other side
of the Triborough.

627
00:28:44.515 --> 00:28:47.309
it ain't gonna cut it with
the Cohiba crowd over here.

628
00:28:47.435 --> 00:28:49.353
I got connects I can tap into
for all that.

629
00:28:49.520 --> 00:28:51.272
To continue my thought.

630
00:28:51.439 --> 00:28:56.277
should I choose to explore
your proposal here.

631
00:28:56.444 --> 00:28:57.778
all I'd be providing

632
00:28:57.945 --> 00:29:01.991
is protection. police.
and permission.

633
00:29:02.908 --> 00:29:05.619
<i>Although. the police piece
will be limited</i>

634
00:29:05.786 --> 00:29:08.080
because they tend
to draw the line

635
00:29:08.247 --> 00:29:10.791
when it comes
to this particular business.

636
00:29:11.417 --> 00:29:12.668
<i>In addition.</i>

637
00:29:12.835 --> 00:29:14.837
I have a big appetite

638
00:29:15.754 --> 00:29:17.840
and I take a very healthy bite.

639
00:29:18.174 --> 00:29:20.134
<i>And as I'm sure you know.</i>

640
00:29:21.260 --> 00:29:23.137
I already got
trusted professionals

641
00:29:23.304 --> 00:29:24.889
doing this work for me.

642
00:29:25.598 --> 00:29:26.724
So...

643
00:29:29.477 --> 00:29:30.936
it's important to me

644
00:29:31.103 --> 00:29:34.190
that you don't step
on their toes.

645
00:29:34.356 --> 00:29:37.151
[tense. dramatic music playing]

646
00:29:37.318 --> 00:29:39.445
It's a big borough.
Mr. Bernardi.

647
00:29:40.154 --> 00:29:41.864
There's room for everybody.

648
00:29:44.116 --> 00:29:45.326
Well...

649
00:29:46.076 --> 00:29:48.412
you'd have to establish
your own customer base

650
00:29:49.205 --> 00:29:52.124
and find a way to move your work
around the city.

651
00:29:52.875 --> 00:29:54.710
I got some thoughts
on that. actually.

652
00:29:55.753 --> 00:29:57.880
What you know about
Flossie Siegel?

653
00:29:58.047 --> 00:29:59.798
[music intensifies]

654
00:29:59.924 --> 00:30:02.134
[music fades]

655
00:30:02.301 --> 00:30:04.386
I know I look like
I was born yesterday

656
00:30:04.553 --> 00:30:06.263
but. believe it or not.

657
00:30:06.430 --> 00:30:08.390
I know a thing or two
about a thing or two.

658
00:30:10.809 --> 00:30:13.562
Those boxes
are filled with trouble. Marvin.

659
00:30:13.687 --> 00:30:14.939
What are you doin'?

660
00:30:19.860 --> 00:30:22.321
We're gonna buy you out of
your share of the club. Shirl.

661
00:30:23.656 --> 00:30:24.990
Me and my sister.

662
00:30:25.533 --> 00:30:27.952
Gonna give you a fair price.

663
00:30:29.745 --> 00:30:31.997
And that's gon' be that.

664
00:30:34.542 --> 00:30:37.670
I suppose this is
a non-negotiable offer.

665
00:30:37.836 --> 00:30:39.046
Like I said.

666
00:30:39.630 --> 00:30:41.173
price is gon' be fair.

667
00:30:45.386 --> 00:30:47.846
I don't think Louis
would have liked this.

668
00:30:51.934 --> 00:30:53.686
Goddamn right about that.

669
00:30:55.479 --> 00:30:56.981
Then why are you doing it?

670
00:30:57.147 --> 00:30:59.316
[solemn music playing]

671
00:31:00.734 --> 00:31:03.112
Because... [sighs]

672
00:31:09.577 --> 00:31:10.911
[sighs]

673
00:31:11.078 --> 00:31:12.496
Lou's not...

674
00:31:13.664 --> 00:31:15.499
Lou's not here no more.

675
00:31:22.256 --> 00:31:23.465
[sighs]

676
00:31:23.632 --> 00:31:24.992
[Kanan] <i>Far as y'all
are concerned.</i>

677
00:31:25.134 --> 00:31:26.468
<i>shit's business as usual.</i>

678
00:31:26.635 --> 00:31:28.429
We just workin' outta here now.

679
00:31:28.596 --> 00:31:30.236
-[man] <i>A'ight.</i>
-[dramatic music playing]

680
00:31:30.347 --> 00:31:31.432
Money stay the same.

681
00:31:31.599 --> 00:31:33.017
Hours don't change.

682
00:31:33.517 --> 00:31:34.602
We back up.

683
00:31:34.768 --> 00:31:35.936
[man laughs]

684
00:31:36.478 --> 00:31:39.231
-[scooter engine revving]
-[chatter]

685
00:31:42.026 --> 00:31:43.485
[Breeze] You double up the Vics?

686
00:31:44.403 --> 00:31:46.280
Also bumped up the Xanax
and the Ritalin.

687
00:31:46.447 --> 00:31:48.198
[pills rattling]

688
00:31:49.325 --> 00:31:51.201
[music transitions
into grim music]

689
00:31:52.369 --> 00:31:53.369
Hmm.

690
00:31:53.746 --> 00:31:55.414
[music fades]

691
00:31:55.581 --> 00:31:56.999
All right.

692
00:31:58.125 --> 00:32:00.085
We'll circle back
in a couple weeks.

693
00:32:08.469 --> 00:32:12.014
[siren wailing nearby]

694
00:32:15.809 --> 00:32:17.728
Can't trust this nigga Breeze.

695
00:32:19.021 --> 00:32:20.481
Hell. can't trust any of 'em.

696
00:32:20.606 --> 00:32:23.150
Breeze. Snaps. Pop.
Lil' Linguini.

697
00:32:23.317 --> 00:32:24.860
See. they don't need us. Kanan.

698
00:32:25.319 --> 00:32:27.297
They just wanna keep you and me
in the fold for a minute

699
00:32:27.321 --> 00:32:28.739
so our crews don't wild
the fuck out

700
00:32:28.906 --> 00:32:30.157
before they put us down.

701
00:32:30.532 --> 00:32:31.825
Ain't how I see it.

702
00:32:32.326 --> 00:32:33.606
You ain't been around
long enough

703
00:32:33.702 --> 00:32:35.382
to even know what the fuck
you seein'. boy.

704
00:32:35.871 --> 00:32:38.832
These niggas ain't our friends.
our partners. or our people.

705
00:32:39.583 --> 00:32:41.960
And we just a means
to an end for them.

706
00:32:42.127 --> 00:32:43.379
Fuck you want. 'Nique?

707
00:32:43.545 --> 00:32:45.047
'Cause I got money to make.

708
00:32:46.006 --> 00:32:48.133
Youngster done drunk
all that Kool-Aid.

709
00:32:50.803 --> 00:32:52.930
I want you and me
to do our own thing.

710
00:32:53.097 --> 00:32:54.390
Fuck these other niggas.

711
00:32:54.556 --> 00:32:56.934
Ain't nothin' for you and me
to do.

712
00:32:57.851 --> 00:32:59.311
We ain't got work without them.

713
00:32:59.728 --> 00:33:01.689
And they about to run
the Southside.

714
00:33:02.940 --> 00:33:05.609
How come you ain't askin' me
about your Uncle Lou?

715
00:33:06.485 --> 00:33:07.778
Streets sayin' I put him down.

716
00:33:07.945 --> 00:33:09.863
but guess you ain't get
that memo.

717
00:33:10.322 --> 00:33:13.367
Fuck is the point in talkin'
'bout shit that can't change?

718
00:33:13.534 --> 00:33:14.535
[scoffs]

719
00:33:15.035 --> 00:33:16.370
Someone dropped
one of my family.

720
00:33:16.495 --> 00:33:18.330
they ain't seein' the sun
come up.

721
00:33:19.540 --> 00:33:21.142
But maybe you ain't beefin'
wit' me like that

722
00:33:21.166 --> 00:33:22.876
'cause you know I didn't do it.

723
00:33:23.502 --> 00:33:26.004
Who put down Lou? Your moms?

724
00:33:26.338 --> 00:33:27.923
'Cause that would be
just like her.

725
00:33:28.674 --> 00:33:30.759
She don't give a fuck
about nobody else.

726
00:33:32.261 --> 00:33:33.887
Or maybe it was Marvin.

727
00:33:35.139 --> 00:33:37.766
Sometimes them brotherly beefs
get real ugly.

728
00:33:38.892 --> 00:33:40.644
Nobody know that shit
better than me.

729
00:33:40.769 --> 00:33:42.771
[grim music playing]

730
00:33:44.148 --> 00:33:45.524
Maybe it was you.

731
00:33:46.567 --> 00:33:48.235
Maybe you and Lou
got into some shit

732
00:33:48.402 --> 00:33:51.697
because you tryin' to break off
from the fam.

733
00:33:54.032 --> 00:33:57.578
So much drama with all y'all.
I can't keep track of that shit.

734
00:33:59.079 --> 00:34:01.457
But you know what they say
about family. man.

735
00:34:02.124 --> 00:34:03.542
<i>Can't live wit' 'em...</i>

736
00:34:04.585 --> 00:34:05.919
can't live wit' em.

737
00:34:11.967 --> 00:34:13.302
[music fades]

738
00:34:14.219 --> 00:34:16.263
<i>♪ Seeing you there
With the next man ♪</i>

739
00:34:16.430 --> 00:34:18.515
<i>♪ Had to flex
For some checks... ♪</i>

740
00:34:18.682 --> 00:34:21.518
You told this nigga 'Nique about
the sit-down at the hospital.

741
00:34:21.685 --> 00:34:24.104
<i>♪ Things were all good
In the hood ♪</i>

742
00:34:24.271 --> 00:34:25.355
Had to be you.

743
00:34:26.023 --> 00:34:27.566
Ain't nobody else knew.

744
00:34:28.525 --> 00:34:30.694
And nobody in that room
gonna talk.

745
00:34:30.944 --> 00:34:32.529
I just asked him if he knew.

746
00:34:33.655 --> 00:34:35.375
Seemed like something
he shoulda been in on.

747
00:34:35.491 --> 00:34:37.451
You stirrin' up trouble. Taz.

748
